  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p>Job Description </p><p>Supervise and coordinate daily construction site activities to ensure work is carried out according to project schedule and drawings.</p><p>Manage and lead site workers, subcontractors, and suppliers to ensure productivity and quality standards are met.</p><p>Ensure compliance with workplace safety, health, and environmental regulations at all times.</p><p>Monitor work progress, materials usage, and manpower deployment.</p><p>Conduct daily site inspections and resolve on-site technical or operational issues.</p><p>Liaise with project managers, engineers, and other stakeholders on site matters.</p><p>Prepare basic site reports, progress updates, and incident reports when required.</p><p>Ensure proper housekeeping and discipline at the construction site.</p><p>Job Requirements </p><p>Minimum 3 years of relevant experience as a Site Supervisor or similar role in the construction industry.</p><p>Familiar with building construction works (e.g. structural works, finishing works, renovation, installation works).</p><p>Knowledge of workplace safety and health regulations; WSH-related certification is an advantage.</p><p>Ability to lead workers and handle daily site operations independently.</p><p>Able to work outdoors and willing to work overtime when required.</p><p>Basic understanding of construction drawings and site instructions.</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
